{"slug": "chant", "root": "chant", "category": "act", "gloss": "rhythmic ritual utterance", "definition": "To chant is to utter words in measured, repeated song — a ritual formula voiced aloud so that its rhythm and sound become part of its power. It differs from ordinary prayer or speech in its cadence: chanting foregrounds the acoustic body of the words, the intoned repetition through which a spell, a psalm, or a name is made to work.", "history": "The root is Latin *cantare*, 'to sing' (a frequentative of *canere*) — the same song hiding inside *enchant*, *incant*, and *incantation*, half the vocabulary of magic traced back to sung Latin. The turn is theoretical: Renaissance magi asked *why* chanting worked, debating whether *incantatio* acted through the natural acoustic properties of sound as a vehicle of *spiritus*, through divine names, or through demons — the very question that divided natural magic from the illicit. The Greek papyri already summon gods 'with this chant,' and monastics chanted psalms to drive out spirits. Sung words, in short, were never merely decorative; Magic's *Chant* effects keep that ritual, repeating pulse.", "def_sources": [{"label": "RenaissanceMagicDB, s.v. incantatio (chanted words producing magical effects)", "where": "RenaissanceMagicDB"}, {"label": "Betz, The Greek Magical Papyri in Translation (call the god with this chant)", "where": "Renaissance magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Etymonline, s.v. chant", "where": "Etymology reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"lang": "Latin", "origin": "Latin cantare 'to sing' (frequentative of canere)", "first": "late 14c.", "note": "The sung root under half the vocabulary of magic — enchant, incant, cantor, and charm's cousin all trace to Latin song.", "hook": "The song hiding in 'enchant', 'incant', and 'chant'."}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 22, "oracle_total": 3, "in_flavor_cards": 22, "in_oracle_cards": 3, "name_match_count": 16, "by_variant": {"chant": 19, "chanting": 4, "chants": 1, "chanted": 1}, "first_year": 1994, "colors": {"G": 11, "B": 11, "W": 8, "C": 1, "U": 3, "R": 10}, "by_year": {"1994": 3, "1996": 3, "1997": 1, "2001": 1, "2003": 1, "2004": 5, "2005": 2, "2006": 2, "2009": 1, "2011": 2, "2012": 1, "2013": 1, "2015": 1, "2017": 1, "2019": 2, "2020": 1, "2022": 1, "2023": 3, "2024": 3, "2025": 3, "2026": 1}}, "cards": [{"id": "506667b1-7922-4959-a5b3-0f8abe8c3615", "name": "Deadbridge Chant", "set": "DSC", "type_line": "Enchantment", "rarity": "mythic", "colors": ["B", "G"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/e/6/e67b8f21-c173-4d1d-8224-2eba4bcc6975.jpg?1782689796", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/e/6/e67b8f21-c173-4d1d-8224-2eba4bcc6975.jpg?1782689796", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/dsc/215/deadbridge-chant?utm_source=api", "local": "img/chant/506667b1-7922-4959-a5b3-0f8abe8c3615.jpg"}, {"id": "be48877f-97b1-4a10-a618-cbc57515e617", "name": "Doubling Chant", "set": "M12", "type_line": "Sorcery", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["G"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/f/7/f71dc232-9b7e-4c0e-ac05-8e48b4936aa9.jpg?1782714869", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/f/7/f71dc232-9b7e-4c0e-ac05-8e48b4936aa9.jpg?1782714869", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/m12/170/doubling-chant?utm_source=api", "local": "img/chant/be48877f-97b1-4a10-a618-cbc57515e617.jpg"}, {"id": "92b44644-cd7b-4568-911c-8a0fdccf4882", "name": "Legion's Chant", "set": "YLCI", "type_line": "Sorcery — Chorus", "rarity": "rare", "colors": ["W"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/a/a/aaae9392-e89c-4075-b9bf-af42c54571ab.jpg?1782731328", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/a/a/aaae9392-e89c-4075-b9bf-af42c54571ab.jpg?1782731328", "scryfall_